## Example 7 — Real-World Series Applications

### Step 1: Analyze the Balloon Problem

Scientific balloon rises 1000 feet in first minute, then each subsequent minute rises 1% more than the previous minute. After an hour, how high?

This is a geometric series with [a_1 = 1000, r = 1.01, n = 60]:

[S_60 = 1000(1.01^60 - 1)/(1.01 - 1) = 1000(1.01^60 - 1)/0.01]

[1.01^60 ≈ 1.967], so [S_60 ≈ 1000(0.967)/0.01 = 96700] feet

This is between 80,000 and 90,000 feet, so yes, it reaches the target height.

